From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Gnoblin Developers <gnoblin@example.invalid>
Date: Mon, 22 Jun 2026 16:00:00 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] wayland: reset stale client cursors on idle focus changes

Wayland clients own the cursor while they have pointer focus. CSD toolkits use
that to set resize cursors at their window edges. If the compositor has no
Wayland surface currently under the pointer, but the old focus has not been
fully invalidated yet, the old client cursor can survive visually until another
client sets a new cursor.

The same can happen when focus moves from a CSD window edge to a layer-shell
surface, because the new surface may not immediately set a cursor. Clear the
old client's cursor state whenever idle pointer focus changes to a different
client; preserve it for same-client surface hops and active button grabs.

Treat "no current surface and no button held" as a compositor/root cursor
situation and unset the client cursor immediately. The button guard preserves
normal implicit-grab behaviour while dragging or resizing.
---
 src/wayland/meta-wayland-pointer.c | 23 +++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 23 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/wayland/meta-wayland-pointer.c b/src/wayland/meta-wayland-pointer.c
index a0ace17..ba6f004 100644
--- a/src/wayland/meta-wayland-pointer.c
+++ b/src/wayland/meta-wayland-pointer.c
@@ -1088,6 +1088,9 @@ meta_wayland_pointer_set_focus (MetaWaylandPointer *pointer,
   ClutterBackend *clutter_backend = meta_backend_get_clutter_backend (backend);
   ClutterSeat *clutter_seat = clutter_backend_get_default_seat (clutter_backend);
   MetaWindow *toplevel_window;
+  struct wl_client *old_client = NULL;
+  struct wl_client *new_client = NULL;
+  gboolean client_changed;
 
   g_return_if_fail (meta_cursor_tracker_get_pointer_visible (cursor_tracker) ||
                     clutter_seat_is_unfocus_inhibited (clutter_seat) ||
@@ -1096,6 +1099,26 @@ meta_wayland_pointer_set_focus (MetaWaylandPointer *pointer,
   if (pointer->focus_surface == surface)
     return;
 
+  if (pointer->focus_surface && pointer->focus_surface->resource)
+    old_client = wl_resource_get_client (pointer->focus_surface->resource);
+  if (surface && surface->resource)
+    new_client = wl_resource_get_client (surface->resource);
+  client_changed = old_client != new_client;
+
+  if (client_changed && pointer->button_count == 0)
+    {
+      if (pointer->cursor_surface)
+        {
+          meta_wayland_surface_update_outputs (pointer->cursor_surface);
+          g_clear_signal_handler (&pointer->cursor_surface_destroy_id,
+                                  pointer->cursor_surface);
+        }
+
+      pointer->cursor_surface = NULL;
+      pointer->cursor_shape = META_CURSOR_INVALID;
+      g_clear_object (&pointer->shape_sprite);
+    }
+
   pointer->last_rel_x = -FLT_MAX;
   pointer->last_rel_y = -FLT_MAX;
 
@@ -1210,6 +1233,9 @@ meta_wayland_pointer_update_cursor_surface (MetaWaylandPointer *pointer)
 
   surface = pointer->focus_surface;
 
+  if (!pointer->current && pointer->button_count == 0)
+    surface = NULL;
+
   if (surface)
     {
       MetaCursorSprite *cursor_sprite = NULL;
-- 
